Finally, you can specify hooks to only run when the model is built in a certain mode such as training and inference mode. You can read more about training an inference mode in [Training and Inference Mode](guides/model_execution/training_and_inference_mode.livemd):

```elixir
model =
  Axon.input("data")
  |> Axon.dense(8)
  |> Axon.attach_hook(&IO.inspect/1, on: :forward, mode: :train)
  |> Axon.relu()

{init_fn, predict_fn} = Axon.build(model, mode: :train)
params = init_fn.(input, %{})
```

